      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAX OFF (8) could finish only among the minors last time (30.10) at Sandown, bringing a two run winning streak to an end. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Drawn out but with clear running expected to go close. ELIJAH ROSE (6) found the going tougher but ran well to place over 525m at The Meadows (30.25) in Grade 5 H. Won an easier race the start before that at Sandown. Has a good record here including four wins. Bold showing expected. ANGRY CHIEF (2) went straight to the front and never headed when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 6th and beaten 7 lengths at Warragul (26.56). Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. URANA ORBIT (1) will be hard to beat with a drop in distance.",
